  "texts": [
    "This can be performed in a few lines of code using Cryptomite, as shown in Figure 7.Extension -As in the QKD example, the RNG case can be improved using other options given in our extractor library, reducing the seed length and allowing the option to relax the requirement on the seed min-entropy rate.",
    "Using our Circulant extractor instead of the Toeplitz extractor saves 581294863 seed bits.",
    "To implement this, the input length n 1 = 6.5 × 10 9 must be adjusted to n ′ 1 such that n ′ 1 + 1 is a prime number with primitive root 2.",
    "Based on this adjustment to n 1, the min-entropy must also be recalculated (using either Theorem 8 or Lemma 1).",
    "We find that the closest prime with primitive root 2 is 6.5 × 10 9 + 69, so we set n ′ 1 = 6.5 × 10 9 + 68 and pad the weak input with 68 fixed bits."
